                    <span>As a former employee of both IBM and AT&T, I lived through years of lack of leadership, innovation and bad management decisions. Lou Gerstner demonstrated that a few common sense principles (listen, customers, focus) go a long way in building a business. I enjoyed the book very much and recommended it to my co-workers.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">A book worthy of be studied on a worthy CEO of a worthy Corp</div>
